-- Barclays names Azar as Middle East chairman
-- By David French
-- Sun Jun 15, 2014 07:04AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, June 15 (Reuters) - British lender Barclays <BARC.L> has named Makram Azar as its chairman for the Middle East and North Africa, a spokesman for the bank confirmed on Sunday.

Azar, who is also global vice chairman of investment banking, has been with Barclays since September 2010, when he joined from private equity firm Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co, according to the lender's website.